We go to BIBIBOP every few weeks and always enjoy their food.  Giving 4 stars this time because it seems they've gotten rid of the regular daikon in favor of a version with chili powder. The first version was, besides the steak, my favorite part of my bowl every time. I hope they bring it back.

Between the various bases, proteins, toppings and sauces there are tons of ways to customize your bowl. Large serving size at affordable prices. Good reward program and the ability to order online for pick-up/delivery. And complementary miso soup!

They really stretch the definition of what could be considered bibibop here. You can get a mishmash of randomly selected ingredients from corn to potatoes on rice here.  The black rice is undercooked, and none of the rice will ever be crispy- it's served in plastic, not a hot stone pot.  The only egg available is scrambled.  They have free miso soup, but you get what you pay for.  It's not inedible, but it's not good.

Had salad with black beans, cooked bean sprouts, steak, kale, pickled cabbage, pickled carrot, kimchee and red sauce.  Free miso soup and extra sauces if you wish. All under $11.  Definitely enjoyed it. Same concept and atmosphere you'd find in any "build-a-bowl" spot in DC.   Friendly staff.

This place serves delicious healthy food. It is something like a chipotle but with completely Asian options. So there’s fried tofu, a variety of raw veggies like carrots, cabbage and an interesting type of radish. The most fascinating items were the purple rice and sweet potato noodles. All in all a great place for a healthy lunch on the go. They also serve miso soup for free.

Aww man, the Bop is the spot. A full meal (and possibly even leftovers) for under $9, with all the goods included. No extra charge for any ingredients in your bowl. Sauce it up with Korean Red hot sauce, yum-yum or teriyaki. Free miso soup. Can’t beat the value.

Think Chipotle, but with "Korean" instead of "Mexican".  You choose a starchy base (noodles, rice) and then toppings.  Then as much sweet chili sauce-- or other sauces, if you don't want the best thing in the world.  It's not as yummy as bibimbap in a blazing hot stone pot, but for fast food, it's pretty OK.

The best meal deal you can get in DC. Bowls in the $7 to $8 range with 15% off vegetarian options on Mondays. Easily two meals. Crunchy, savory, healthy, filling and fast. I have to restrain myself from eating here as much as I'd like to avoid burning out on it.

Can cheap fast food be delicious, fresh, and nutritious? This place answers this question with an unequivocal Yes! You choose what you want in your bowl, pay 8 bucks or less and enjoy a free miso soup. Like your meals extra saucy? Just select from the plethora of Asian sauces by the soda machines. Feel like a healthy drink too? Try the fresh lemonade or tea. But first, if you haven’t been yet, come here immediately!

(Translated by Google) I just discovered this little improved fast food, in the same vein as Chipotle but Korean version. Fresh products, well cooked, I could taste the seasoned sauces before making up my mind. The generous portions and the free miso soup, available in self-service, will ensure you are stalled for a moment! Perfect for the aftermath of well-watered evenings;) I'll be back! Korean fast casual. Great, fast bibimbap bowls.  Prices are reasonable and the atmosphere is cozy (for a fast food restaurant).  The beef lettuce bowl with everything and onion sauce (see pic) was a delicious and satisfying lunch.  PS: The restaurant just opened (June 06, 17)  in the space where ShopHouse used to be. The décor is the same and the food is similar, but more focused in concept and (mostly) healthier.
